IRA S. BUSHEY & SONS, Inc., Libelant-Appellee, v. HURON STEVEDORING COMPANY, Respondent-Appellant. Eugene F. Gilligan and John J. Heckman, StipulatorsAppellants. No. 320. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. April 4, 1933. L. De Grove Potter, of New York City, for appellant. James A. Martin, of New York City, for appellee.

Before MANTON, L. HAND, and CHASE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Decree (1 F. Supp. 327) affirmed in open court.
